th Kenya scooping 11 in the French capital.Half of the line-up at the men's 200m where Tebogo excelled were athletes from Africa, with the continent rising as a contender in shorter events beyond its dominance at longer distances.AFP His gold as well as silver in the men's 4x400m relay, boosted the country's total Olympic medal tally to four.Outside the airport, traditional dancers wearing animal skins and beads kicked off a welcoming ceremony that was to later continue at the national stadium.Related NewsFCTA targets rural communities to sustain Nigeria's HIV responseCAC warns Nigerians against fake companies, lists unregistered firmsCIPMN warns against financial waste in unregulated projectsMasisi had already granted the country of 2.3 million people half a day off to party on August 9.Tebogo is only the second African athlete to win an Olympic medal in the men's 200m, after Namibian Frankie Fredericks took silver in Atlanta in 1996.Botswana won their first Olympic medal at the 2012 London Games when Nijel Amos took silver in the 800m.\", \"from\": 8176, \"to\": 9404, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8219, \"end\": 8224, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.7140084098317173, \"rank\": 0.40054351544630534, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}, {\"begin\": 8353, \"end\": 8358, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya\", \"score\": 0.9999999995443432, \"rank\": 3.816035966687136e-10, \"text\": \"Kenya\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya\"}, {\"begin\": 8378, \"end\": 8384, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9665437332341005, \"rank\": 0.03313672193010008, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/reso